<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1094,1589]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,387,1094,1120]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Nomenclatural notes</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitter, G." box="[420,571,1094,1120]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter (1919)</bibRefCitation>
cited three gatherings in the protologue: 
<emphasis box="[1051,1188,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Pittier 2281</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1205,1355,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Williams 818</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Tonduz 14727,</emphasis>
and he cited the herbaria housing the specimens he examined (and sometimes the accession number). We were able to locate part of the original material that he examined at the herbaria G-BOIS and 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1197,1166,1192]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
: 
<emphasis box="[1210,1346,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Pittier 2281</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1364,1401,1166,1192]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
No. 676535 [annotated by Bitter as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" box="[485,645,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminiflora">
<emphasis box="[485,645,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. geminiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
], 
<collectingCountry box="[667,703,1202,1228]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
No. 676536 [not found at 
<collectingCountry box="[996,1037,1202,1229]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
]); 
<emphasis box="[1065,1211,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Williams 818</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1262,1202,1228]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
No. 678304 [not found at 
<collectingCountry box="[236,277,1238,1265]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
]); 
<emphasis box="[305,462,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Tonduz 14727</emphasis>
(G-BOIS-00415144! [annotated by Bitter as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitter (1919: 496)" authorityName="Bitter" authorityPageNumber="496" authorityYear="1919" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="heteroclita" subSpecies="coalescens">
<emphasis box="[972,1122,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. heteroclita</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1179,1300,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">coalescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bitter, G." pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter (1919: 496)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
]. The original material pertaining to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" box="[603,895,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="heteroclita" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[603,753,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. heteroclita</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[809,895,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is problematic in that part of it is missing and the 
<specimenCount box="[136,303,1310,1337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
that we were able to locate were annotated by Bitter with a different name. Despite having annotated the 
<collectingCountry box="[180,216,1346,1372]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
specimen of 
<emphasis box="[373,510,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Pittier 2281</emphasis>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" box="[552,715,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminiflora">
<emphasis box="[552,715,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. geminiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specimen label specifies the floral color (violet) mentioned in Bitter’s description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" box="[424,720,1382,1409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="heteroclita" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[424,575,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. heteroclita</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[634,720,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which differs from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" box="[1032,1194,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminiflora">
<emphasis box="[1032,1194,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. geminiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(white). Therefore the specimen of 
<emphasis box="[286,423,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Pittier 2281</emphasis>
at 
<collectingCountry box="[454,490,1418,1444]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[508,545,1418,1444]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">US</collectingCountry>
No. 676535) is selected here as the 
<typeStatus box="[976,1079,1418,1444]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">lectotype</typeStatus>
for the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="heteroclita" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1247,1400,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. heteroclita</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[136,225,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[225,229,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1094,1589]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,390,1490,1516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:—This variety of the widespread 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Sendtner" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[773,923,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heteroclita">
<emphasis box="[773,923,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">L. heteroclita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1156,1278,1490,1516]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1332,1421,1491,1517]" name="Panama" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Panama</collectingCountry>
as a variant with purple, stellate corollas (as opposed to the more common white color found further north). This color variant is the only color variant known from 
<collectingCountry box="[638,760,1562,1588]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[815,904,1563,1589]" name="Panama" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Panama</collectingCountry>
and merits further study.
</paragraph>
